responsive to conventional therapy. Penicillamine is used as a form of immunosuppression to treat rheumatoid arthritis. Penicillamine inhibits macrophages, decreases IL-1 and the number of T-lymphocytes, and prevents collagen cross linkage. In Wilson''s disease it binds copper, allowing it to be eliminated in the urine.', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
